{
  "text": "The \u03b2 invariant \u03b2(M ) of a matroid M is the coefficient of x in T (M ; x, y). Annan [CITATION_1] showed that computing \u03b2(M ) for a graphic matroid is a #P-hard problem. The following corollary of the previous proof shows a different situation for bicircular matroids.",
